285 g Shaved Beef
4 tbsp Soy Sauce Mirin Blend
1 unit(s) Yellow Onion
2 unit(s) Green Onion
1 tbsp Seasoned Rice Vinegar
2 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
¾ cup Sticky Rice
2 unit(s) Egg
2 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
113 g Carrot, julienned
56 g Snow Peas
7 g Black Sesame Seeds
2 tbsp Sugar*
½ tbsp Oil*
⅓ tsp Salt*
1 tbsp Butter*

Wash and dry all produce.
To a medium pot, add 1 1/4 cups (2 1/2 cups) water and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) salt. Cover and bring to a boil over high.
Using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
To the boiling water, add rice. Stir, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 13-15 min, until rice is tender and water is absorbed. Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Cut cucumbers into 1/4-inch rounds.
To a medium microwaveable bowl, add vinegar, 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) sugar and a pinch of salt. (NOTE: This is your pickling liquid.) Microwave in 15 sec increments, stirring between each, until sugar dissolves. Add cucumbers, then stir to combine.

Peel, then cut yellow onion into 1/4-inch pieces.
Thinly slice green onions.
Trim, then halve snow peas.
Line a plate with paper towels.
Snip off one corner of beef package. Carefully drain and discard liquid. Transfer beef to the prepared plate.
Using tongs or a fork, separate layers of beef. Pat beef with paper towels to dry.
To another medium bowl, add beef, yellow onions, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) sugar and half the soy sauce mirin blend. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat. Set aside.

Heat a large non-stick pan over high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil and beef. Cook for 3-4 min, stirring occasionally and separating beef as needed, until beef is browned.**
Add remaining soy sauce mirin blend, beef broth concentrate, snow peas, carrots and 1/2 cup (1 cup) water. Bring to a simmer over medium. Cook for 4-5 min, stirring occasionally, until slightly reduced.
Remove from heat.

In a medium non-stick pan (use a large pan for 4 servings), melt 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter over medium.
Crack eggs into the pan, then sprinkle with sesame seeds. Season with salt and pepper. Pan-fry 2-3 min, covered, until egg whites are set. (NOTE: Yolks will still be runny.)

Season rice with salt, then fluff with a fork.
Divide rice between bowls.
Divide beef over top of rice and spoon sauce from the pan over top.
Divide eggs over top of beef.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Served pickled cucumbers on the side.